West 125th Street, at the North (Hudson) River. The photographer is viewing southeastward to show across Claremont heights the Riverside Baptist Church and Grants Tomb. The viaduct shown carries automotive traffic of Riverside Drive across this gap; the low bridge-like structure, the New York Central Railroad tracks.

June 6, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

Eighth Avenue, east side, between W. 125th and 126th Streets, showing a two story frame building that bears No. 2338. Bromleys Atlas of 1922 gives this as No. 2346. The brick building at the right is the 4-story Bishop Building, located at the N. E. corner of 125th Street. Overhead is the Ninth Avenue Elevated Line.
May 5, 1940
Views 1,2
